  <Name>k__BackingField: Proverbs
  fancyName: 
  nickname: pro
  language: English
  lang: eng
  version: New Living Translation
  ver: NLT
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: The Purpose of Proverbs
      content: "These are the proverbs of Solomon, David\u2019s son, king of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their purpose is to teach people wisdom and discipline,\n\tto help
        them understand the insights of the wise.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their purpose is to teach people to live disciplined and successful
        lives,\n\tto help them do what is right, just, and fair.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These proverbs will give insight to the simple,\n\tknowledge and
        discernment to the young.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let the wise listen to these proverbs and become even wiser.\n\tLet
        those with understanding receive guidance  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "by exploring the meaning in these proverbs and parables,\n\tthe words
        of the wise and their riddles.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the foundation of true
        knowledge,\n\tbut fools despise wisdom and discipline.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "A Father\u2019s Exhortation: Acquire Wisdom"
      content: "My child,[COMMENT[0]] listen when your father corrects you.\n\tDon\u2019t
        neglect your mother\u2019s instruction.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'My son; '
        - ft: also in 1:10, 15.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "What you learn from them will crown you with grace\n\tand be a chain
        of honor around your neck.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, if sinners entice you,\n\tturn your back on them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They may say, \u201CCome and join us.\n\tLet\u2019s hide and kill
        someone!\n\tJust for fun, let\u2019s ambush the innocent!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let\u2019s swallow them alive, like the grave[COMMENT[0]];\n\tlet\u2019s
        swallow them whole, like those who go down to the pit of death.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: like Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "Think of the great things we\u2019ll get!\n\tWe\u2019ll fill our
        houses with all the stuff we take.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come, throw in your lot with us;\n\twe\u2019ll all share the loot.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, don\u2019t go along with them!\n\tStay far away from their
        paths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They rush to commit evil deeds.\n\tThey hurry to commit murder.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If a bird sees a trap being set,\n\tit knows to stay away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But these people set an ambush for themselves;\n\tthey are trying
        to get themselves killed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Such is the fate of all who are greedy for money;\n\tit robs them
        of life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Wisdom Shouts in the Streets
      content: "Wisdom shouts in the streets.\n\tShe cries out in the public square.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She calls to the crowds along the main street,\n\tto those gathered
        in front of the city gate:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long, you simpletons,\n\twill you insist on being simpleminded?\n\tHow
        long will you mockers relish your mocking?\n\tHow long will you fools hate
        knowledge?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come and listen to my counsel.\n\tI\u2019ll share my heart with you\n\tand
        make you wise.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI called you so often, but you wouldn\u2019t come.\n\tI reached
        out to you, but you paid no attention.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You ignored my advice\n\tand rejected the correction I offered.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will laugh when you are in trouble!\n\tI will mock you when
        disaster overtakes you\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "when calamity overtakes you like a storm,\n\twhen disaster engulfs
        you like a cyclone,\n\tand anguish and distress overwhelm you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen they cry for help, I will not answer.\n\tThough they anxiously
        search for me, they will not find me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they hated knowledge\n\tand chose not to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They rejected my advice\n\tand paid no attention when I corrected
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, they must eat the bitter fruit of living their own way,\n\tchoking
        on their own schemes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For simpletons turn away from me\u2014to death.\n\tFools are destroyed
        by their own complacency.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But all who listen to me will live in peace,\n\tuntroubled by fear
        of harm.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Benefits of Wisdom
      content: "My child,[COMMENT[0]] listen to what I say,\n\tand treasure my commands.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: My son.
    - title: 
      content: "Tune your ears to wisdom,\n\tand concentrate on understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Cry out for insight,\n\tand ask for understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Search for them as you would for silver;\n\tseek them like hidden
        treasures.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will understand what it means to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tand
        you will gain knowledge of God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> grants wisdom!\n\tFrom his mouth
        come knowledge and understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He grants a treasure of common sense to the honest.\n\tHe is a shield
        to those who walk with integrity.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He guards the paths of the just\n\tand protects those who are faithful
        to him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will understand what is right, just, and fair,\n\tand you
        will find the right way to go.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For wisdom will enter your heart,\n\tand knowledge will fill you
        with joy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wise choices will watch over you.\n\tUnderstanding will keep you
        safe.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wisdom will save you from evil people,\n\tfrom those whose words
        are twisted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These men turn from the right way\n\tto walk down dark paths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They take pleasure in doing wrong,\n\tand they enjoy the twisted
        ways of evil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their actions are crooked,\n\tand their ways are wrong.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wisdom will save you from the immoral woman,\n\tfrom the seductive
        words of the promiscuous woman.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She has abandoned her husband\n\tand ignores the covenant she made
        before God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Entering her house leads to death;\n\tit is the road to the grave.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to the spirits of the dead.
    - title: 
      content: "The man who visits her is doomed.\n\tHe will never reach the paths
        of life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So follow the steps of the good,\n\tand stay on the paths of the
        righteous.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For only the godly will live in the land,\n\tand those with integrity
        will remain in it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the wicked will be removed from the land,\n\tand the treacherous
        will be uprooted."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Lord
      content: "My child,[COMMENT[0]] never forget the things I have taught you.\n\tStore
        my commands in your heart.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'My son; '
        - ft: also in 3:11, 21.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "If you do this, you will live many years,\n\tand your life will be
        satisfying.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Never let loyalty and kindness leave you!\n\tTie them around your
        neck as a reminder.\n\tWrite them deep within your heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will find favor with both God and people,\n\tand you will
        earn a good reputation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with all your heart;\n\tdo
        not depend on your own understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Seek his will in all you do,\n\tand he will show you which path to
        take.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be impressed with your own wisdom.\n\tInstead, fear the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and turn away from evil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will have healing for your body\n\tand strength for your
        bones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Honor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with your wealth\n\tand with
        the best part of everything you produce.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he will fill your barns with grain,\n\tand your vats will overflow
        with good wine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, don\u2019t reject the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        discipline,\n\tand don\u2019t be upset when he corrects you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> corrects those he loves,\n\tjust
        as a father corrects a child in whom he delights.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'loves, / and he punishes those he accepts as his children. '
        - ft: Compare Heb 12:6.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Joyful is the person who finds wisdom,\n\tthe one who gains understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For wisdom is more profitable than silver,\n\tand her wages are better
        than gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wisdom is more precious than rubies;\n\tnothing you desire can compare
        with her.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She offers you long life in her right hand,\n\tand riches and honor
        in her left.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She will guide you down delightful paths;\n\tall her ways are satisfying.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wisdom is a tree of life to those who embrace her;\n\thappy are those
        who hold her tightly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "By wisdom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> founded the earth;\n\tby
        understanding he created the heavens.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "By his knowledge the deep fountains of the earth burst forth,\n\tand
        the dew settles beneath the night sky.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, don\u2019t lose sight of common sense and discernment.\n\tHang
        on to them,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for they will refresh your soul.\n\tThey are like jewels on a necklace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They keep you safe on your way,\n\tand your feet will not stumble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You can go to bed without fear;\n\tyou will lie down and sleep soundly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You need not be afraid of sudden disaster\n\tor the destruction that
        comes upon the wicked,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is your security.\n\tHe will
        keep your foot from being caught in a trap.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not withhold good from those who deserve it\n\twhen it\u2019s
        in your power to help them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you can help your neighbor now, don\u2019t say,\n\t\u201CCome
        back tomorrow, and then I\u2019ll help you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t plot harm against your neighbor,\n\tfor those who live
        nearby trust you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t pick a fight without reason,\n\twhen no one has done you
        harm.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t envy violent people\n\tor copy their ways.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Such wicked people are detestable to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tbut
        he offers his friendship to the godly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> curses the house of the wicked,\n\tbut
        he blesses the home of the upright.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> mocks the mockers\n\tbut is gracious
        to the humble.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:34 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'The '
        - ft: Compare Jas 4:6; 1 Pet 5:5.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "The wise inherit honor,\n\tbut fools are put to shame!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "A Father\u2019s Wise Advice"
      content: "My children,[COMMENT[0]] listen when your father corrects you.\n\tPay
        attention and learn good judgment,  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: My sons.
    - title: 
      content: "for I am giving you good guidance.\n\tDon\u2019t turn away from my
        instructions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I, too, was once my father\u2019s son,\n\ttenderly loved as my
        mother\u2019s only child.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My father taught me,\n\t\u201CTake my words to heart.\n\tFollow my
        commands, and you will live.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Get wisdom; develop good judgment.\n\tDon\u2019t forget my words
        or turn away from them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t turn your back on wisdom, for she will protect you.\n\tLove
        her, and she will guard you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Getting wisdom is the wisest thing you can do!\n\tAnd whatever else
        you do, develop good judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you prize wisdom, she will make you great.\n\tEmbrace her, and
        she will honor you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She will place a lovely wreath on your head;\n\tshe will present
        you with a beautiful crown.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child,[COMMENT[0]] listen to me and do as I say,\n\tand you will
        have a long, good life.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'My son; '
        - ft: also in 4:20.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I will teach you wisdom\u2019s ways\n\tand lead you in straight paths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you walk, you won\u2019t be held back;\n\twhen you run, you
        won\u2019t stumble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Take hold of my instructions; don\u2019t let them go.\n\tGuard them,
        for they are the key to life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t do as the wicked do,\n\tand don\u2019t follow the path
        of evildoers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t even think about it; don\u2019t go that way.\n\tTurn away
        and keep moving.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For evil people can\u2019t sleep until they\u2019ve done their evil
        deed for the day.\n\tThey can\u2019t rest until they\u2019ve caused someone
        to stumble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They eat the food of wickedness\n\tand drink the wine of violence!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The way of the righteous is like the first gleam of dawn,\n\twhich
        shines ever brighter until the full light of day.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the way of the wicked is like total darkness.\n\tThey have no
        idea what they are stumbling over.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, pay attention to what I say.\n\tListen carefully to my
        words.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t lose sight of them.\n\tLet them penetrate deep into your
        heart,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for they bring life to those who find them,\n\tand healing to their
        whole body.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Guard your heart above all else,\n\tfor it determines the course
        of your life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Avoid all perverse talk;\n\tstay away from corrupt speech.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look straight ahead,\n\tand fix your eyes on what lies before you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Mark out a straight path for your feet;\n\tstay on the safe path.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t get sidetracked;\n\tkeep your feet from following evil."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Avoid Immoral Women
      content: "My son, pay attention to my wisdom;\n\tlisten carefully to my wise
        counsel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will show discernment,\n\tand your lips will express what
        you\u2019ve learned.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the lips of an immoral woman are as sweet as honey,\n\tand her
        mouth is smoother than oil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But in the end she is as bitter as poison,\n\tas dangerous as a double-edged
        sword.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Her feet go down to death;\n\ther steps lead straight to the grave.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "For she cares nothing about the path to life.\n\tShe staggers down
        a crooked trail and doesn\u2019t realize it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now, my sons, listen to me.\n\tNever stray from what I am about
        to say:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Stay away from her!\n\tDon\u2019t go near the door of her house!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you do, you will lose your honor\n\tand will lose to merciless
        people all you have achieved.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Strangers will consume your wealth,\n\tand someone else will enjoy
        the fruit of your labor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the end you will groan in anguish\n\twhen disease consumes your
        body.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will say, \u201CHow I hated discipline!\n\tIf only I had not
        ignored all the warnings!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, why didn\u2019t I listen to my teachers?\n\tWhy didn\u2019t I
        pay attention to my instructors?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have come to the brink of utter ruin,\n\tand now I must face public
        disgrace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Drink water from your own well\u2014\n\tshare your love only with
        your wife.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Drink water from your own cistern, / flowing water from your own
            well.
    - title: 
      content: "Why spill the water of your springs in the streets,\n\thaving sex
        with just anyone?[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Why spill your springs in the streets, / your streams in the city
            squares?
    - title: 
      content: "You should reserve it for yourselves.\n\tNever share it with strangers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let your wife be a fountain of blessing for you.\n\tRejoice in the
        wife of your youth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She is a loving deer, a graceful doe.\n\tLet her breasts satisfy
        you always.\n\tMay you always be captivated by her love.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why be captivated, my son, by an immoral woman,\n\tor fondle the
        breasts of a promiscuous woman?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sees clearly what a man does,\n\texamining
        every path he takes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "An evil man is held captive by his own sins;\n\tthey are ropes that
        catch and hold him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will die for lack of self-control;\n\the will be lost because
        of his great foolishness."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Lessons for Daily Life
      content: "My child,[COMMENT[0]] if you have put up security for a friend\u2019s
        debt\n\tor agreed to guarantee the debt of a stranger\u2014  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: My son.
    - title: 
      content: "if you have trapped yourself by your agreement\n\tand are caught
        by what you said\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "follow my advice and save yourself,\n\tfor you have placed yourself
        at your friend\u2019s mercy.\n\tNow swallow your pride;\n\tgo and beg to
        have your name erased.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t put it off; do it now!\n\tDon\u2019t rest until you do.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Save yourself like a gazelle escaping from a hunter,\n\tlike a bird
        fleeing from a net.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Take a lesson from the ants, you lazybones.\n\tLearn from their ways
        and become wise!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though they have no prince\n\tor governor or ruler to make them work,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "they labor hard all summer,\n\tgathering food for the winter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you, lazybones, how long will you sleep?\n\tWhen will you wake
        up?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A little extra sleep, a little more slumber,\n\ta little folding
        of the hands to rest\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then poverty will pounce on you like a bandit;\n\tscarcity will attack
        you like an armed robber.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What are worthless and wicked people like?\n\tThey are constant liars,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "signaling their deceit with a wink of the eye,\n\ta nudge of the
        foot, or the wiggle of fingers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their perverted hearts plot evil,\n\tand they constantly stir up
        trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But they will be destroyed suddenly,\n\tbroken in an instant beyond
        all hope of healing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There are six things the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> hates\u2014\n\tno,
        seven things he detests:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "haughty eyes,\n\ta lying tongue,\n\thands that kill the innocent,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "a heart that plots evil,\n\tfeet that race to do wrong,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "a false witness who pours out lies,\n\ta person who sows discord
        in a family.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My son, obey your father\u2019s commands,\n\tand don\u2019t neglect
        your mother\u2019s instruction.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Keep their words always in your heart.\n\tTie them around your neck.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you walk, their counsel will lead you.\n\tWhen you sleep, they
        will protect you.\n\tWhen you wake up, they will advise you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For their command is a lamp\n\tand their instruction a light;\n\ttheir
        corrective discipline\n\tis the way to life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It will keep you from the immoral woman,\n\tfrom the smooth tongue
        of a promiscuous woman.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t lust for her beauty.\n\tDon\u2019t let her coy glances
        seduce you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For a prostitute will bring you to poverty,[COMMENT[0]]but sleeping
        with another man\u2019s wife will cost you your life.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:26 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to a loaf of bread.
    - title: 
      content: "Can a man scoop a flame into his lap\n\tand not have his clothes
        catch on fire?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can he walk on hot coals\n\tand not blister his feet?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So it is with the man who sleeps with another man\u2019s wife.\n\tHe
        who embraces her will not go unpunished.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Excuses might be found for a thief\n\twho steals because he is starving.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if he is caught, he must pay back seven times what he stole,\n\teven
        if he has to sell everything in his house.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the man who commits adultery is an utter fool,\n\tfor he destroys
        himself.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will be wounded and disgraced.\n\tHis shame will never be erased.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the woman\u2019s jealous husband will be furious,\n\tand he will
        show no mercy when he takes revenge.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will accept no compensation,\n\tnor be satisfied with a payoff
        of any size."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Another Warning about Immoral Women
      content: "Follow my advice, my son;\n\talways treasure my commands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Obey my commands and live!\n\tGuard my instructions as you guard
        your own eyes.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: as the pupil of your eye.
    - title: 
      content: "Tie them on your fingers as a reminder.\n\tWrite them deep within
        your heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Love wisdom like a sister;\n\tmake insight a beloved member of your
        family.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let them protect you from an affair with an immoral woman,\n\tfrom
        listening to the flattery of a promiscuous woman.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While I was at the window of my house,\n\tlooking through the curtain,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I saw some naive young men,\n\tand one in particular who lacked common
        sense.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He was crossing the street near the house of an immoral woman,\n\tstrolling
        down the path by her house.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It was at twilight, in the evening,\n\tas deep darkness fell.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The woman approached him,\n\tseductively dressed and sly of heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She was the brash, rebellious type,\n\tnever content to stay at home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She is often in the streets and markets,\n\tsoliciting at every corner.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She threw her arms around him and kissed him,\n\tand with a brazen
        look she said,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI\u2019ve just made my peace offerings\n\tand fulfilled my
        vows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You\u2019re the one I was looking for!\n\tI came out to find you,
        and here you are!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My bed is spread with beautiful blankets,\n\twith colored sheets
        of Egyptian linen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I\u2019ve perfumed my bed\n\twith myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come, let\u2019s drink our fill of love until morning.\n\tLet\u2019s
        enjoy each other\u2019s caresses,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for my husband is not home.\n\tHe\u2019s away on a long trip.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He has taken a wallet full of money with him\n\tand won\u2019t return
        until later this month.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: until the moon is full.
    - title: 
      content: "So she seduced him with her pretty speech\n\tand enticed him with
        her flattery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He followed her at once,\n\tlike an ox going to the slaughter.\n\tHe
        was like a stag caught in a trap,[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:22 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads '
          body: slaughter, as shackles are for the discipline of a fool.
    - title: 
      content: "awaiting the arrow that would pierce its heart.\n\tHe was like a
        bird flying into a snare,\n\tlittle knowing it would cost him his life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So listen to me, my sons,\n\tand pay attention to my words.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let your hearts stray away toward her.\n\tDon\u2019t wander
        down her wayward path.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For she has been the ruin of many;\n\tmany men have been her victims.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Her house is the road to the grave.[COMMENT[0]]Her bedroom is the
        den of death.
      comments:
