        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to Sheol.
  - verses:
    - title: Wisdom Calls for a Hearing
      content: "Listen as Wisdom calls out!\n\tHear as understanding raises her voice!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "On the hilltop along the road,\n\tshe takes her stand at the crossroads.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "By the gates at the entrance to the town,\n\ton the road leading
        in, she cries aloud,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI call to you, to all of you!\n\tI raise my voice to all people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You simple people, use good judgment.\n\tYou foolish people, show
        some understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to me! For I have important things to tell you.\n\tEverything
        I say is right,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for I speak the truth\n\tand detest every kind of deception.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My advice is wholesome.\n\tThere is nothing devious or crooked in
        it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My words are plain to anyone with understanding,\n\tclear to those
        with knowledge.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Choose my instruction rather than silver,\n\tand knowledge rather
        than pure gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For wisdom is far more valuable than rubies.\n\tNothing you desire
        can compare with it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, Wisdom, live together with good judgment.\n\tI know where
        to discover knowledge and discernment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All who fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will hate evil.\n\tTherefore,
        I hate pride and arrogance,\n\tcorruption and perverse speech.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Common sense and success belong to me.\n\tInsight and strength are
        mine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Because of me, kings reign,\n\tand rulers make just decrees.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rulers lead with my help,\n\tand nobles make righteous judgments.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version read '
          body: and nobles are judges over the earth.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI love all who love me.\n\tThose who search will surely find
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have riches and honor,\n\tas well as enduring wealth and justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My gifts are better than gold, even the purest gold,\n\tmy wages
        better than sterling silver!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I walk in righteousness,\n\tin paths of justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who love me inherit wealth.\n\tI will fill their treasuries.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> formed me from the beginning,\n\tbefore
        he created anything else.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was appointed in ages past,\n\tat the very first, before the earth
        began.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was born before the oceans were created,\n\tbefore the springs
        bubbled forth their waters.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Before the mountains were formed,\n\tbefore the hills, I was born\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "before he had made the earth and fields\n\tand the first handfuls
        of soil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was there when he established the heavens,\n\twhen he drew the
        horizon on the oceans.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was there when he set the clouds above,\n\twhen he established
        springs deep in the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was there when he set the limits of the seas,\n\tso they would
        not spread beyond their boundaries.\n\tAnd when he marked off the earth\u2019s
        foundations,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was the architect at his side.\n\tI was his constant delight,\n\trejoicing
        always in his presence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And how happy I was with the world he created;\n\thow I rejoiced
        with the human family!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd so, my children,[COMMENT[0]] listen to me,\n\tfor all who
        follow my ways are joyful.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:32 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: my sons.
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to my instruction and be wise.\n\tDon\u2019t ignore it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Joyful are those who listen to me,\n\twatching for me daily at my
        gates,\n\twaiting for me outside my home!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For whoever finds me finds life\n\tand receives favor from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But those who miss me injure themselves.\n\tAll who hate me love
        death.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Wisdom has built her house;\n\tshe has carved its seven columns.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She has prepared a great banquet,\n\tmixed the wines, and set the
        table.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She has sent her servants to invite everyone to come.\n\tShe calls
        out from the heights overlooking the city.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome in with me,\u201D she urges the simple.\n\tTo those who
        lack good judgment, she says,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome, eat my food,\n\tand drink the wine I have mixed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Leave your simple ways behind, and begin to live;\n\tlearn to use
        good judgment.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Anyone who rebukes a mocker will get an insult in return.\n\tAnyone
        who corrects the wicked will get hurt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So don\u2019t bother correcting mockers;\n\tthey will only hate you.\n\tBut
        correct the wise,\n\tand they will love you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instruct the wise,\n\tand they will be even wiser.\n\tTeach the righteous,\n\tand
        they will learn even more.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the foundation of wisdom.\n\tKnowledge
        of the Holy One results in good judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wisdom will multiply your days\n\tand add years to your life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you become wise, you will be the one to benefit.\n\tIf you scorn
        wisdom, you will be the one to suffer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Folly Calls for a Hearing
      content: "The woman named Folly is brash.\n\tShe is ignorant and doesn\u2019t
        know it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She sits in her doorway\n\ton the heights overlooking the city.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She calls out to men going by\n\twho are minding their own business.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome in with me,\u201D she urges the simple.\n\tTo those who
        lack good judgment, she says,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CStolen water is refreshing;\n\tfood eaten in secret tastes
        the best!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But little do they know that the dead are there.\n\tHer guests are
        in the depths of the grave.[COMMENT[0]]"
      comments:
      - number: '9:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: in Sheol.
  - verses:
    - title: The Proverbs of Solomon
      content: "The proverbs of Solomon:\n\tA wise child[COMMENT[0]] brings joy to
        a father;\n\ta foolish child brings grief to a mother.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'son; '
        - ft: also in 10:1b.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Tainted wealth has no lasting value,\n\tbut right living can save
        your life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not let the godly go hungry,\n\tbut
        he refuses to satisfy the craving of the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Lazy people are soon poor;\n\thard workers get rich.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A wise youth harvests in the summer,\n\tbut one who sleeps during
        harvest is a disgrace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godly are showered with blessings;\n\tthe words of the wicked
        conceal violent intentions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We have happy memories of the godly,\n\tbut the name of a wicked
        person rots away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wise are glad to be instructed,\n\tbut babbling fools fall flat
        on their faces.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People with integrity walk safely,\n\tbut those who follow crooked
        paths will be exposed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People who wink at wrong cause trouble,\n\tbut a bold reproof promotes
        peace.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: but babbling fools fall flat on their faces.
