      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> detests the use of dishonest scales,\n\tbut
        he delights in accurate weights.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pride leads to disgrace,\n\tbut with humility comes wisdom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Honesty guides good people;\n\tdishonesty destroys treacherous people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Riches won\u2019t help on the day of judgment,\n\tbut right living
        can save you from death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godly are directed by honesty;\n\tthe wicked fall beneath their
        load of sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godliness of good people rescues them;\n\tthe ambition of treacherous
        people traps them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the wicked die, their hopes die with them,\n\tfor they rely
        on their own feeble strength.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godly are rescued from trouble,\n\tand it falls on the wicked
        instead.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "With their words, the godless destroy their friends,\n\tbut knowledge
        will rescue the righteous.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The whole city celebrates when the godly succeed;\n\tthey shout for
        joy when the wicked die.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Upright citizens are good for a city and make it prosper,\n\tbut
        the talk of the wicked tears it apart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is foolish to belittle one\u2019s neighbor;\n\ta sensible person
        keeps quiet.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A gossip goes around telling secrets,\n\tbut those who are trustworthy
        can keep a confidence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Without wise leadership, a nation falls;\n\tthere is safety in having
        many advisers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There\u2019s danger in putting up security for a stranger\u2019s
        debt;\n\tit\u2019s safer not to guarantee another person\u2019s debt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A gracious woman gains respect,\n\tbut ruthless men gain only wealth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your kindness will reward you,\n\tbut your cruelty will destroy you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Evil people get rich for the moment,\n\tbut the reward of the godly
        will last.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Godly people find life;\n\tevil people find death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> detests people with crooked hearts,\n\tbut
        he delights in those with integrity.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Evil people will surely be punished,\n\tbut the children of the godly
        will go free.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A beautiful woman who lacks discretion\n\tis like a gold ring in
        a pig\u2019s snout.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godly can look forward to a reward,\n\twhile the wicked can expect
        only judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Give freely and become more wealthy;\n\tbe stingy and lose everything.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The generous will prosper;\n\tthose who refresh others will themselves
        be refreshed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People curse those who hoard their grain,\n\tbut they bless the one
        who sells in time of need.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you search for good, you will find favor;\n\tbut if you search
        for evil, it will find you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Trust in your money and down you go!\n\tBut the godly flourish like
        leaves in spring.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who bring trouble on their families inherit the wind.\n\tThe
        fool will be a servant to the wise.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The seeds of good deeds become a tree of life;\n\ta wise person wins
        friends.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
