    - title: 
      content: "Commit yourself to instruction;\n\tlisten carefully to words of knowledge.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t fail to discipline your children.\n\tThe rod of punishment
        won\u2019t kill them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Physical discipline\n\tmay well save them from death.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: from Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "My child,[COMMENT[0]] if your heart is wise,\n\tmy own heart will
        rejoice!  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'My son; '
        - ft: also in 23:19.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Everything in me will celebrate\n\twhen you speak what is right.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t envy sinners,\n\tbut always continue to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be rewarded for this;\n\tyour hope will not be disappointed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, listen and be wise:\n\tKeep your heart on the right course.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not carouse with drunkards\n\tor feast with gluttons,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for they are on their way to poverty,\n\tand too much sleep clothes
        them in rags.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to your father, who gave you life,\n\tand don\u2019t despise
        your mother when she is old.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Get the truth and never sell it;\n\talso get wisdom, discipline,
        and good judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The father of godly children has cause for joy.\n\tWhat a pleasure
        to have children who are wise.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:24 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to have a wise son.
    - title: 
      content: "So give your father and mother joy!\n\tMay she who gave you birth
        be happy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O my son, give me your heart.\n\tMay your eyes take delight in following
        my ways.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A prostitute is a dangerous trap;\n\ta promiscuous woman is as dangerous
        as falling into a narrow well.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She hides and waits like a robber,\n\teager to make more men unfaithful.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who has anguish? Who has sorrow?\n\tWho is always fighting? Who is
        always complaining?\n\tWho has unnecessary bruises? Who has bloodshot eyes?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is the one who spends long hours in the taverns,\n\ttrying out
        new drinks.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t gaze at the wine, seeing how red it is,\n\thow it sparkles
        in the cup, how smoothly it goes down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For in the end it bites like a poisonous snake;\n\tit stings like
        a viper.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will see hallucinations,\n\tand you will say crazy things.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will stagger like a sailor tossed at sea,\n\tclinging to a swaying
        mast.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you will say, \u201CThey hit me, but I didn\u2019t feel it.\n\tI
        didn\u2019t even know it when they beat me up.\n\tWhen will I wake up\n\tso
        I can look for another drink?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t envy evil people\n\tor desire their company.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For their hearts plot violence,\n\tand their words always stir up
        trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A house is built by wisdom\n\tand becomes strong through good sense.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Through knowledge its rooms are filled\n\twith all sorts of precious
        riches and valuables.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wise are mightier than the strong,[COMMENT[0]]and those with
        knowledge grow stronger and stronger.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: A wise man is strength.
    - title: 
      content: "So don\u2019t go to war without wise guidance;\n\tvictory depends
        on having many advisers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wisdom is too lofty for fools.\n\tAmong leaders at the city gate,
        they have nothing to say.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A person who plans evil\n\twill get a reputation as a troublemaker.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The schemes of a fool are sinful;\n\teveryone detests a mocker.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you fail under pressure,\n\tyour strength is too small.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rescue those who are unjustly sentenced to die;\n\tsave them as they
        stagger to their death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t excuse yourself by saying, \u201CLook, we didn\u2019t
        know.\u201D\n\tFor God understands all hearts, and he sees you.\n\tHe who
        guards your soul knows you knew.\n\tHe will repay all people as their actions
        deserve.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child,[COMMENT[0]] eat honey, for it is good,\n\tand the honeycomb
        is sweet to the taste.  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'My son; '
        - ft: also in 24:21.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "In the same way, wisdom is sweet to your soul.\n\tIf you find it,
        you will have a bright future,\n\tand your hopes will not be cut short.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t wait in ambush at the home of the godly,\n\tand don\u2019t
        raid the house where the godly live.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godly may trip seven times, but they will get up again.\n\tBut
        one disaster is enough to overthrow the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t rejoice when your enemies fall;\n\tdon\u2019t be happy
        when they stumble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be displeased with you\n\tand
        will turn his anger away from them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t fret because of evildoers;\n\tdon\u2019t envy the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For evil people have no future;\n\tthe light of the wicked will be
        snuffed out.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the king.\n\tDon\u2019t
        associate with rebels,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for disaster will hit them suddenly.\n\tWho knows what punishment
        will come\n\tfrom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the king?  "
      comments: []
    - title: More Sayings of the Wise
      content: "Here are some further sayings of the wise:\n\tIt is wrong to show
        favoritism when passing judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A judge who says to the wicked, \u201CYou are innocent,\u201D\n\twill
        be cursed by many people and denounced by the nations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But it will go well for those who convict the guilty;\n\trich blessings
        will be showered on them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "An honest answer\n\tis like a kiss of friendship.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do your planning and prepare your fields\n\tbefore building your
        house.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t testify against your neighbors without cause;\n\tdon\u2019t
        lie about them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And don\u2019t say, \u201CNow I can pay them back for what they\u2019ve
        done to me!\n\tI\u2019ll get even with them!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I walked by the field of a lazy person,\n\tthe vineyard of one with
        no common sense.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I saw that it was overgrown with nettles.\n\tIt was covered with
        weeds,\n\tand its walls were broken down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then, as I looked and thought about it,\n\tI learned this lesson:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A little extra sleep, a little more slumber,\n\ta little folding
        of the hands to rest\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then poverty will pounce on you like a bandit;\n\tscarcity will attack
        you like an armed robber."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: More Proverbs of Solomon
      content: 'These are more proverbs of Solomon, collected by the advisers of
        King Hezekiah of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is God\u2019s privilege to conceal things\n\tand the king\u2019s
        privilege to discover them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No one can comprehend the height of heaven, the depth of the earth,\n\tor
        all that goes on in the king\u2019s mind!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Remove the impurities from silver,\n\tand the sterling will be ready
        for the silversmith.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Remove the wicked from the king\u2019s court,\n\tand his reign will
        be made secure by justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t demand an audience with the king\n\tor push for a place
        among the great.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s better to wait for an invitation to the head table\n\tthan
        to be sent away in public disgrace.\n\tJust because you\u2019ve seen something,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "don\u2019t be in a hurry to go to court.\n\tFor what will you do
        in the end\n\tif your neighbor deals you a shameful defeat?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When arguing with your neighbor,\n\tdon\u2019t betray another person\u2019s
        secret.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Others may accuse you of gossip,\n\tand you will never regain your
        good reputation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Timely advice is lovely,\n\tlike golden apples in a silver basket.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "To one who listens, valid criticism\n\tis like a gold earring or
        other gold jewelry.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Trustworthy messengers refresh like snow in summer.\n\tThey revive
        the spirit of their employer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A person who promises a gift but doesn\u2019t give it\n\tis like
        clouds and wind that bring no rain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Patience can persuade a prince,\n\tand soft speech can break bones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do you like honey?\n\tDon\u2019t eat too much, or it will make you
        sick!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t visit your neighbors too often,\n\tor you will wear out
        your welcome.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Telling lies about others\n\tis as harmful as hitting them with an
        ax,\n\twounding them with a sword,\n\tor shooting them with a sharp arrow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Putting confidence in an unreliable person in times of trouble\n\tis
        like chewing with a broken tooth or walking on a lame foot.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Singing cheerful songs to a person with a heavy heart\n\tis like
        taking someone\u2019s coat in cold weather\n\tor pouring vinegar in a wound.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: pouring vinegar on soda.
    - title: 
      content: "If your enemies are hungry, give them food to eat.\n\tIf they are
        thirsty, give them water to drink.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will heap burning coals of shame on their heads,\n\tand the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will reward you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As surely as a north wind brings rain,\n\tso a gossiping tongue causes
        anger!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s better to live alone in the corner of an attic\n\tthan
        with a quarrelsome wife in a lovely home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Good news from far away\n\tis like cold water to the thirsty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If the godly give in to the wicked,\n\tit\u2019s like polluting a
        fountain or muddying a spring.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s not good to eat too much honey,\n\tand it\u2019s not good
        to seek honors for yourself.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A person without self-control\n\tis like a city with broken-down
        walls."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Honor is no more associated with fools\n\tthan snow with summer or
        rain with harvest.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Like a fluttering sparrow or a darting swallow,\n\tan undeserved
        curse will not land on its intended victim.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Guide a horse with a whip, a donkey with a bridle,\n\tand a fool
        with a rod to his back!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t answer the foolish arguments of fools,\n\tor you will
        become as foolish as they are.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Be sure to answer the foolish arguments of fools,\n\tor they will
        become wise in their own estimation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Trusting a fool to convey a message\n\tis like cutting off one\u2019s
        feet or drinking poison!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A proverb in the mouth of a fool\n\tis as useless as a paralyzed
        leg.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Honoring a fool\n\tis as foolish as tying a stone to a slingshot.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A proverb in the mouth of a fool\n\tis like a thorny branch brandished
        by a drunk.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "An employer who hires a fool or a bystander\n\tis like an archer
        who shoots at random.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As a dog returns to its vomit,\n\tso a fool repeats his foolishness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There is more hope for fools\n\tthan for people who think they are
        wise.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The lazy person claims, \u201CThere\u2019s a lion on the road!\n\tYes,
        I\u2019m sure there\u2019s a lion out there!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As a door swings back and forth on its hinges,\n\tso the lazy person
        turns over in bed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Lazy people take food in their hand\n\tbut don\u2019t even lift it
        to their mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Lazy people consider themselves smarter\n\tthan seven wise counselors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Interfering in someone else\u2019s argument\n\tis as foolish as yanking
        a dog\u2019s ears.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Just as damaging\n\tas a madman shooting a deadly weapon  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "is someone who lies to a friend\n\tand then says, \u201CI was only
        joking.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fire goes out without wood,\n\tand quarrels disappear when gossip
        stops.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A quarrelsome person starts fights\n\tas easily as hot embers light
        charcoal or fire lights wood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rumors are dainty morsels\n\tthat sink deep into one\u2019s heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Smooth[COMMENT[0]] words may hide a wicked heart,\n\tjust as a pretty
        glaze covers a clay pot.  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:23 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek version; Hebrew reads '
          body: Burning.
    - title: 
      content: "People may cover their hatred with pleasant words,\n\tbut they\u2019re
        deceiving you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They pretend to be kind, but don\u2019t believe them.\n\tTheir hearts
        are full of many evils.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:25 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: seven evils.
    - title: 
      content: "While their hatred may be concealed by trickery,\n\ttheir wrongdoing
        will be exposed in public.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you set a trap for others,\n\tyou will get caught in it yourself.\n\tIf
        you roll a boulder down on others,\n\tit will crush you instead.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A lying tongue hates its victims,\n\tand flattering words cause ruin."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t brag about tomorrow,\n\tsince you don\u2019t know what
        the day will bring.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let someone else praise you, not your own mouth\u2014\n\ta stranger,
        not your own lips.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A stone is heavy and sand is weighty,\n\tbut the resentment caused
        by a fool is even heavier.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Anger is cruel, and wrath is like a flood,\n\tbut jealousy is even
        more dangerous.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "An open rebuke\n\tis better than hidden love!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wounds from a sincere friend\n\tare better than many kisses from
        an enemy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A person who is full refuses honey,\n\tbut even bitter food tastes
        sweet to the hungry.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A person who strays from home\n\tis like a bird that strays from
        its nest.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The heartfelt counsel of a friend\n\tis as sweet as perfume and incense.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Never abandon a friend\u2014\n\teither yours or your father\u2019s.\n\tWhen
        disaster strikes, you won\u2019t have to ask your brother for assistance.\n\tIt\u2019s
        better to go to a neighbor than to a brother who lives far away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Be wise, my child,[COMMENT[0]] and make my heart glad.\n\tThen I
        will be able to answer my critics.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: my son.
    - title: 
      content: "A prudent person foresees danger and takes precautions.\n\tThe simpleton
        goes blindly on and suffers the consequences.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Get security from someone who guarantees a stranger\u2019s debt.\n\tGet
        a deposit if he does it for foreigners.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek and Latin versions (see also 20:16); Hebrew reads '
          body: for a promiscuous woman.
    - title: 
      content: "A loud and cheerful greeting early in the morning\n\twill be taken
        as a curse!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A quarrelsome wife is as annoying\n\tas constant dripping on a rainy
        day.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Stopping her complaints is like trying to stop the wind\n\tor trying
        to hold something with greased hands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As iron sharpens iron,\n\tso a friend sharpens a friend.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As workers who tend a fig tree are allowed to eat the fruit,\n\tso
        workers who protect their employer\u2019s interests will be rewarded.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As a face is reflected in water,\n\tso the heart reflects the real
        person.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Just as Death and Destruction[COMMENT[0]] are never satisfied,\n\tso
        human desire is never satisfied.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Sheol and Abaddon.
    - title: 
      content: "Fire tests the purity of silver and gold,\n\tbut a person is tested
        by being praised.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: by flattery.
    - title: 
      content: "You cannot separate fools from their foolishness,\n\teven though
        you grind them like grain with mortar and pestle.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Know the state of your flocks,\n\tand put your heart into caring
        for your herds,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for riches don\u2019t last forever,\n\tand the crown might not be
        passed to the next generation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After the hay is harvested and the new crop appears\n\tand the mountain
        grasses are gathered in,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "your sheep will provide wool for clothing,\n\tand your goats will
        provide the price of a field.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you will have enough goats\u2019 milk for yourself,\n\tyour family,
        and your servant girls."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "The wicked run away when no one is chasing them,\n\tbut the godly
        are as bold as lions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When there is moral rot within a nation, its government topples easily.\n\tBut
        wise and knowledgeable leaders bring stability.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A poor person who oppresses the poor\n\tis like a pounding rain that
        destroys the crops.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "To reject the law is to praise the wicked;\n\tto obey the law is
        to fight them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Evil people don\u2019t understand justice,\n\tbut those who follow
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> understand completely.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Better to be poor and honest\n\tthan to be dishonest and rich.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Young people who obey the law are wise;\n\tthose with wild friends
        bring shame to their parents.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: their father.
    - title: 
      content: "Income from charging high interest rates\n\twill end up in the pocket
        of someone who is kind to the poor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God detests the prayers\n\tof a person who ignores the law.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who lead good people along an evil path\n\twill fall into their
        own trap,\n\tbut the honest will inherit good things.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rich people may think they are wise,\n\tbut a poor person with discernment
        can see right through them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the godly succeed, everyone is glad.\n\tWhen the wicked take
        charge, people go into hiding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People who conceal their sins will not prosper,\n\tbut if they confess
        and turn from them, they will receive mercy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Blessed are those who fear to do wrong,[COMMENT[0]]but the stubborn
        are headed for serious trouble.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'those who fear the '
        - ft: 'Hebrew reads '
          body: those who fear.
    - title: 
      content: "A wicked ruler is as dangerous to the poor\n\tas a roaring lion or
        an attacking bear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A ruler with no understanding will oppress his people,\n\tbut one
        who hates corruption will have a long life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A murderer\u2019s tormented conscience will drive him into the grave.\n\tDon\u2019t
        protect him!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The blameless will be rescued from harm,\n\tbut the crooked will
        be suddenly destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A hard worker has plenty of food,\n\tbut a person who chases fantasies
        ends up in poverty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The trustworthy person will get a rich reward,\n\tbut a person who
        wants quick riches will get into trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Showing partiality is never good,\n\tyet some will do wrong for a
        mere piece of bread.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Greedy people try to get rich quick\n\tbut don\u2019t realize they\u2019re
        headed for poverty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the end, people appreciate honest criticism\n\tfar more than flattery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Anyone who steals from his father and mother\n\tand says, \u201CWhat\u2019s
        wrong with that?\u201D\n\tis no better than a murderer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Greed causes fighting;\n\ttrusting the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        leads to prosperity.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who trust their own insight are foolish,\n\tbut anyone who
        walks in wisdom is safe.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Whoever gives to the poor will lack nothing,\n\tbut those who close
        their eyes to poverty will be cursed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the wicked take charge, people go into hiding.\n\tWhen the wicked
        meet disaster, the godly flourish."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "Whoever stubbornly refuses to accept criticism\n\twill suddenly be
        destroyed beyond recovery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the godly are in authority, the people rejoice.\n\tBut when
        the wicked are in power, they groan.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The man who loves wisdom brings joy to his father,\n\tbut if he hangs
        around with prostitutes, his wealth is wasted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A just king gives stability to his nation,\n\tbut one who demands
        bribes destroys it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "To flatter friends\n\tis to lay a trap for their feet.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Evil people are trapped by sin,\n\tbut the righteous escape, shouting
        for joy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godly care about the rights of the poor;\n\tthe wicked don\u2019t
        care at all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Mockers can get a whole town agitated,\n\tbut the wise will calm
        anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If a wise person takes a fool to court,\n\tthere will be ranting
        and ridicule but no satisfaction.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The bloodthirsty hate blameless people,\n\tbut the upright seek to
        help them.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'The bloodthirsty hate blameless people, / and they seek to kill
            the upright; '
        - ft: 'Hebrew reads '
          body: The bloodthirsty hate blameless people; / as for the upright, they
            seek their life.
    - title: 
      content: "Fools vent their anger,\n\tbut the wise quietly hold it back.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If a ruler pays attention to liars,\n\tall his advisers will be wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The poor and the oppressor have this in common\u2014\n\tthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gives sight to the eyes of both.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If a king judges the poor fairly,\n\this throne will last forever.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "To discipline a child produces wisdom,\n\tbut a mother is disgraced
        by an undisciplined child.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the wicked are in authority, sin flourishes,\n\tbut the godly
        will live to see their downfall.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Discipline your children, and they will give you peace of mind\n\tand
        will make your heart glad.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When people do not accept divine guidance, they run wild.\n\tBut
        whoever obeys the law is joyful.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Words alone will not discipline a servant;\n\tthe words may be understood,
        but they are not heeded.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There is more hope for a fool\n\tthan for someone who speaks without
        thinking.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A servant pampered from childhood\n\twill become a rebel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "An angry person starts fights;\n\ta hot-tempered person commits all
        kinds of sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pride ends in humiliation,\n\twhile humility brings honor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you assist a thief, you only hurt yourself.\n\tYou are sworn to
        tell the truth, but you dare not testify.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fearing people is a dangerous trap,\n\tbut trusting the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        means safety.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Many seek the ruler\u2019s favor,\n\tbut justice comes from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The righteous despise the unjust;\n\tthe wicked despise the godly."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Sayings of Agur
      content: "The sayings of Agur son of Jakeh contain this message.[COMMENT[0]]I
        am weary, O God;\n\tI am weary and worn out, O God.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'son of Jakeh from Massa; '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: son of Jakeh, an oracle.
      - number: '30:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'The Hebrew can also be translated '
          body: The man declares this to Ithiel, / to Ithiel and to Ucal.
    - title: 
      content: "I am too stupid to be human,\n\tand I lack common sense.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have not mastered human wisdom,\n\tnor do I know the Holy One.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who but God goes up to heaven and comes back down?\n\tWho holds the
        wind in his fists?\n\tWho wraps up the oceans in his cloak?\n\tWho has created
        the whole wide world?\n\tWhat is his name\u2014and his son\u2019s name?\n\tTell
        me if you know!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Every word of God proves true.\n\tHe is a shield to all who come
        to him for protection.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not add to his words,\n\tor he may rebuke you and expose you as
        a liar.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O God, I beg two favors from you;\n\tlet me have them before I die.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "First, help me never to tell a lie.\n\tSecond, give me neither poverty
        nor riches!\n\tGive me just enough to satisfy my needs.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For if I grow rich, I may deny you and say, \u201CWho is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?\u201D\n\tAnd
        if I am too poor, I may steal and thus insult God\u2019s holy name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Never slander a worker to the employer,\n\tor the person will curse
        you, and you will pay for it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Some people curse their father\n\tand do not thank their mother.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are pure in their own eyes,\n\tbut they are filthy and unwashed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They look proudly around,\n\tcasting disdainful glances.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They have teeth like swords\n\tand fangs like knives.\n\tThey devour
        the poor from the earth\n\tand the needy from among humanity.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The leech has two suckers\n\tthat cry out, \u201CMore, more!\u201D[COMMENT[0]]There
        are three things that are never satisfied\u2014\n\tno, four that never say,
        \u201CEnough!\u201D:  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "two daughters who cry out, \u201CGive, give!\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: "the grave,[COMMENT[0]]the barren womb,\n\tthe thirsty desert,\n\tthe
        blazing fire.  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "The eye that mocks a father\n\tand despises a mother\u2019s instructions\n\twill
        be plucked out by ravens of the valley\n\tand eaten by vultures.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There are three things that amaze me\u2014\n\tno, four things that
        I don\u2019t understand:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "how an eagle glides through the sky,\n\thow a snake slithers on a
        rock,\n\thow a ship navigates the ocean,\n\thow a man loves a woman.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "An adulterous woman consumes a man,\n\tthen wipes her mouth and says,
        \u201CWhat\u2019s wrong with that?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There are three things that make the earth tremble\u2014\n\tno, four
        it cannot endure:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "a slave who becomes a king,\n\tan overbearing fool who prospers,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "a bitter woman who finally gets a husband,\n\ta servant girl who
        supplants her mistress.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There are four things on earth that are small but unusually wise:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ants\u2014they aren\u2019t strong,\n\tbut they store up food all
        summer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hyraxes[COMMENT[0]]\u2014they aren\u2019t powerful,\n\tbut they make
        their homes among the rocks.  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:26 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Coneys, '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: Rock badgers.
    - title: 
      content: "Locusts\u2014they have no king,\n\tbut they march in formation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Lizards\u2014they are easy to catch,\n\tbut they are found even in
        kings\u2019 palaces.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There are three things that walk with stately stride\u2014\n\tno,
        four that strut about:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the lion, king of animals, who won\u2019t turn aside for anything,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the strutting rooster,\n\tthe male goat,\n\ta king as he leads his
        army.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you have been a fool by being proud or plotting evil,\n\tcover
        your mouth in shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As the beating of cream yields butter\n\tand striking the nose causes
        bleeding,\n\tso stirring up anger causes quarrels."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Sayings of King Lemuel
      content: 'The sayings of King Lemuel contain this message,[COMMENT[0]] which
        his mother taught him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'of Lemuel, king of Massa; '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: of King Lemuel, an oracle.
    - title: 
      content: "O my son, O son of my womb,\n\tO son of my vows,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "do not waste your strength on women,\n\ton those who ruin kings.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is not for kings, O Lemuel, to guzzle wine.\n\tRulers should not
        crave alcohol.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For if they drink, they may forget the law\n\tand not give justice
        to the oppressed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Alcohol is for the dying,\n\tand wine for those in bitter distress.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let them drink to forget their poverty\n\tand remember their troubles
        no more.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Speak up for those who cannot speak for themselves;\n\tensure justice
        for those being crushed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, speak up for the poor and helpless,\n\tand see that they get
        justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Wife of Noble Character
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]Who can find a virtuous and capable wife?\n\tShe is
        more precious than rubies.  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '31:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 10-31 comprise a Hebrew acrostic poem; each verse begins with
            a successive letter of the Hebrew alphabet.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Her husband can trust her,\n\tand she will greatly enrich his life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She brings him good, not harm,\n\tall the days of her life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She finds wool and flax\n\tand busily spins it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She is like a merchant\u2019s ship,\n\tbringing her food from afar.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She gets up before dawn to prepare breakfast for her household\n\tand
        plan the day\u2019s work for her servant girls.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She goes to inspect a field and buys it;\n\twith her earnings she
        plants a vineyard.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She is energetic and strong,\n\ta hard worker.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She makes sure her dealings are profitable;\n\ther lamp burns late
        into the night.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Her hands are busy spinning thread,\n\ther fingers twisting fiber.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She extends a helping hand to the poor\n\tand opens her arms to the
        needy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She has no fear of winter for her household,\n\tfor everyone has
        warm[COMMENT[0]] clothes.  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in Greek and Latin versions; Hebrew reads '
          body: scarlet.
    - title: 
      content: "She makes her own bedspreads.\n\tShe dresses in fine linen and purple
        gowns.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Her husband is well known at the city gates,\n\twhere he sits with
        the other civic leaders.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She makes belted linen garments\n\tand sashes to sell to the merchants.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She is clothed with strength and dignity,\n\tand she laughs without
        fear of the future.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When she speaks, her words are wise,\n\tand she gives instructions
        with kindness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She carefully watches everything in her household\n\tand suffers
        nothing from laziness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Her children stand and bless her.\n\tHer husband praises her:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThere are many virtuous and capable women in the world,\n\tbut
        you surpass them all!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Charm is deceptive, and beauty does not last;\n\tbut a woman who
        fears the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be greatly praised.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Reward her for all she has done.\n\tLet her deeds publicly declare
        her praise."
      comments: []
